---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Reference Materials" description="Frameworks, principles, and practical guides for Open Science policy and strategy.">
  <header class="masthead" style="background-image: url('/assets/img/background-image-blue.png'); background-size: cover; height: 40vh; min-height: 300px;">
    <div class="container h-100">
      <div class="row h-100 align-items-center justify-content-center text-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10 align-self-end">
          <h1 class="text-white font-weight-bold" style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);">Reference Materials</h1>
          <hr class="divider my-4" style="border-color: #ffd100; border-width: 3px; max-width: 50px;" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-8 align-self-baseline">
          <p class="text-white-75 font-weight-light" style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);">
            Ground your work in trusted definitions, policies, and frameworks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">
      
      <!-- Intro / Definition -->
      <div class="row mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto text-center">
            <p class="lead text-muted">
                Use these resources to align definitions, inform institutional policy, and build a shared vocabulary for Open Science support.
            </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 1: Frameworks & Principles -->
      <div class="row mb-4">
          <div class="col-12">
              <h3 class="section-heading text-uppercase text-primary mb-4 border-bottom pb-2">Frameworks & Principles</h3>
              <p class="text-muted mb-4">Essential documents for understanding the "Why" and "What" of global Open Science.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="col-lg-4 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-left-dark shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">UNESCO Recommendation</h5>
                    <span class="badge badge-light border mb-2">Policy</span>
                    <p class="card-text small">The global standard defining Open Science as an inclusive construct combining open knowledge, infrastructure, and societal engagement.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.unesco.org/en/open-science/about" target="_blank" class="stretched-link"></a>
                </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-4 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-left-success shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title text-success">FAIR Principles</h5>
                    <span class="badge badge-light border mb-2">Data Management</span>
                    <p class="card-text small">Guiding principles for making research data <strong>F</strong>indable, <strong>A</strong>ccessible, <strong>I</strong>nteroperable, and <strong>R</strong>eusable. The standard for machine-actionable data.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.go-fair.org/fair-principles/" target="_blank" class="stretched-link"></a>
                </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-4 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-left-warning shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title text-warning" style="color: #d39e00 !important;">CARE Principles</h5>
                    <span class="badge badge-light border mb-2">Ethics & Equity</span>
                    <p class="card-text small">Indigenous data governance principles (Collective Benefit, Authority to Control, Responsibility, Ethics) that complement FAIR by centering people and purpose.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.gida-global.org/care" target="_blank" class="stretched-link"></a>
                </div>
            </div>
          </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 2: Cookbooks & Guides -->
      <div class="row mt-5">
          <div class="col-12">
              <h3 class="section-heading text-uppercase text-info mb-4 border-bottom pb-2">Practical Guides</h3>
              <p class="text-muted mb-4">"How-to" references for designing library services and workflows.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
            <div class="card h-100 border-left-primary shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
                        <h5 class="card-title text-primary">ACRL Open Science Cookbook</h5>
                        <i class="fas fa-book-open fa-2x text-black-50"></i>
                    </div>
                    <p class="card-text mt-3">
                        A comprehensive collection of "recipes" (case studies) for open science support. Use this to find concrete examples of services you can implement at your institution.
                    </p>
                    <a href="https://www.ala.org/news/2025/06/new-acrl-open-science-cookbook" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm mt-2">Access the Cookbook</a>
                </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Placeholder for Glossary or other guides -->
          <div class="col-lg-6 mb-4">
             <div class="card h-100 border-left-info shadow-sm bg-light">
                <div class="card-body d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center text-muted">
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <i class="fas fa-tools fa-2x mb-2"></i>
                        <p class="mb-0">More guides coming soon...</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
             </div>
          </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
.border-left-dark { border-left: 5px solid #343a40; }
.border-left-primary { border-left: 5px solid #007bff; }
.border-left-success { border-left: 5px solid #28a745; }
.border-left-warning { border-left: 5px solid #ffc107; }
.border-left-info { border-left: 5px solid #17a2b8; }
</style>
